Code to calculate ePRS-IR-PFC-STR

The script could be run using R or command prompt. Please specify the names and locations for the
following files:
Summarystats_IR_PFC_STR.txt – list of SNPs selected from the GTEx (PFC)
GENODATA (in PLINK binary format) – genodata file
OUTPUT – name of the output file

Rscript $PWD/PRSice.R --prsice $PWD/PRSice_linux --base $PWD/Sumstats_IR_PFC_STR.txt --snp rsid --pvalue p-value --stat beta --A1 effect_allele --A2 non_effect_allele --target $PWD/GENODATA --no-regress --clump-kb 500  —clump-r2 0.2  --clump-p 1  --print-snp  --bar-levels 1.0 --fastscore --model add --score sum --missing SET_ZERO --thread max --out $PWD/OUTPUT
Please refer to https://choishingwan.github.io/PRSice/ for more details on how to install and use PRSice.
Genodata is to be provided in PLINK binary format (bed/bim/fam).

Output files are the following:
• *.snp – list of SNPs included in the calculated score,
• *.all.score – contains calculated score for each subject

PRSice https://choishingwan.github.io/PRSice/
Choi SW, and O’Reilly PF. "PRSice-2: Polygenic Risk Score Software for Biobank-Scale Data." GigaScience 8, no. 7 (July 1, 2019). https://doi.org/10.1093/gigascience/giz082.
